        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>12 Upper Gower St</placeName>
                    <date>May 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.—</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have the honour to transmit as on former occasions, for the approval of the Lords Commissioners of Her Majesty’s Treasury, the account of M<hi rend="superscript">rss</hi>. Smith &amp; Elder for the second and third numbers of the First Part of the “Zoology of the Voyage of the Beagle”, both of which are now published.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I beg leave to state, that as before I have examined the accounts, and superintended the expenditure of each part.—</p>
<p>I have the honour to remain | Sir | Your obedient servant | Charles Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To | A. Y. Spearman Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></p>
<p>Treasury Chambers.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Preserved with this letter are two accounts from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>., dated 1 March 1839 and 1 May 1839, detailing the various costs of <hi rend="italic">Fossil Mammalia,</hi> Nos. 2 and 3. The total expenses were £57 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and £51 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. respectively.</note>
        </div>        
            
